          <summary>How does it Work?</summary>
          <p>Each round of the competition requires the candidate to explore and communicate what they care about, why they care and how they plan to make a difference if empowered financially.</p>

          <p>The Founders of Charitable Heroes personally guarantee that the winner will be able to give away $300 each year for their rest of their lives. Each year Charitable Heroes colloborates with the competition winner to support a person, cause or organization with $300. </p>

           <p>Registration fees are used to cover operational and promotional expenses required to execute the competition. In the event that we surpass these expenses, excess revenue will result in a bigger annual financial award for our competition winner. The order of magnitude of this bigger financial award is determined by the number of entrants the competition finds, so we need your help! Applicant entry fees build a pool of money, if we attract enough entrants the annual award could be $50,000 annually - imagine the difference that person would make! It would create a real-life superhero. What would you do with that kind of power? Who would you help? Regardless, we are excited to empower one winner financially to a small degree, and to empower everyone else with a deeper knowledge of what matters to them, and how they can make a difference. For now, the grand prize is only $300 annually as a starting point.</p>

          <p>The selection process occurs throughout the course of the competition over three rounds. During each round a judge is assigned to CandidatesThe submission of the candidate is scored during each round on a scale of 0-100 and feedback is provided by the judge. Candidates are eliminated after each round and one winner is chosen.</p>
