          <b>Your Superpowers</b>
          <p>Our competition awards one winner with "charitable superpowers" - which we define as: The ability to give away money every year, to any cause, person or ogranization where it creates a positive impact regardless of your personal financial status." One winner will have the ability to give away $300 every year for the rest of their lives.</p>
        </details>
      </li>

<li>
        <details class=''>
          <summary>How do you try to expand philanthropy?</summary>
          <p>Our competition winner can provide financial support (via gift, investment or purchase) to any entity type (public, private or hybrid). This is different from the traditional philanthropist using a donor advised fund. Today, many budding philanthropists look to start a donor advised fund but this limits how they can provide support. Today's challenges are often complicated and require a philanthropic approach which is more open-minded and unencumbered. 

          Our marketing is targeted towards youth leaders. We believe life-long empowerment through philanthropy is important for molding future leaders. Most philanthropists are older. We wanted to turn that on it's head and give one young adult a lifetime of financial power to make a difference.
          </p>
        </details>
